<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14117">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Inventing.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11288">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      In your own words, define inventing. Then do the following: <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/n5h01jhICwQ" target="_blank"
        >What Is Invention (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11288 mb-requirement-id-11289">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the role of inventors and their inventions
        in the economic development of the United States. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/sSBq9A9GwAk" target="_blank"
          >The Industrial Revolution: Inventions and Changes (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/FGwdpJrfTec" target="_blank"
          >What Is Economic Development (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11288 mb-requirement-id-11290">
        (b) List three inventions and state how they have helped humankind.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TepBC9dWQZM" target="_blank"
          >Top 5 Inventions That Changed the World (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/lcc-HnMmsXA" target="_blank"
          >7 Inventions That Changed The World (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11291">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11291 mb-requirement-id-11292">
        (a) With your parent or guardian's permission and counselor's approval,
        interview an adult who has invented a useful item or process. Report
        what you learned to your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.invent.org/inductees" target="_blank"
          >National Inventors Hall of Fame Inductees Have Changed the World
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11291 mb-requirement-id-11293">
        (b) Read about three inventors. Select the one you find most interesting
        and tell your counselor what you learned.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11294">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11294 mb-requirement-id-11295">
        (a) Define the term intellectual property. Explain which government
        agencies oversee the protection of intellectual property, the types of
        intellectual property that can be protected, how such property is
        protected, and why protection is necessary. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rDKxuTi2Cmk" target="_blank"
          >What Is Intellectual Property &amp; Why Do I Care (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Ay9fZMUPCnE" target="_blank"
          >Intellectual Propert Law: The Basics of Patent Law (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bQbW_XEYibs" target="_blank"
          >Tips for Protecting Your Business's Intellectual Property (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11294 mb-requirement-id-11296">
        (b) Explain the components of a patent and the different types of
        patents available. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/lERq71WVjgM" target="_blank"
          >What Are the Types of Patents? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11294 mb-requirement-id-11297">
        (c) Examine your Scouting gear and find a patent number on a camping
        item you have used. With your parent or guardian's permission, use the
        internet to find out more about that patent. Compare the finished item
        with the claims and drawings in the patent. Report what you learned to
        your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://ppubs.uspto.gov/basic/" target="_blank"
          >US Patent and Trade Office Basic Search (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11294 mb-requirement-id-11298">
        (d) Explain to your counselor the term patent infringement. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/o5nlV9OSgyg" target="_blank"
          >Patent Infringement (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11306">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor the types of inventions that are appropriate
      to share with others, and explain why. Tell your counselor about one
      unpatented invention and its impact on society. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/B8PuOS0J6Ro" target="_blank"
        >Unlucky Inventors Who Never Got To Cash In (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11307">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Choose a commercially available product that you have used on an overnight
      camping trip with your troop. Make recommendations for improving the
      product, and make a sketch that shows your recommendations. Discuss your
      recommendations with your counselor.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11299">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Think of an item you would like to invent that would solve a problem for
      your family, troop, chartered organization, community, or a
      special-interest group. Then do the following, while keeping a notebook to
      record your progress. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/StdwWpbokcw" target="_blank"
        >Inventing 101 (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/ERFgorcRCJY" target="_blank"
        >Little Inventors: How To Think Up Invention Ideas (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/JJU_Echi2tk" target="_blank"
        >Turning Imagination into Reality (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11299 mb-requirement-id-11300">
        (a) Talk to potential users of your invention and determine their needs.
        Then, based on what you have learned, write a statement describing the
        invention and how it would help solve a problem. This statement should
        include a detailed sketch of the invention. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kT0ZqwdPYRM" target="_blank"
          >User Needs Statement in Design Thinking (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/l0hVIH3EnlQ" target="_blank"
          >The Secret to Successfully Pitching an Idea (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ooBRwIDQRdw" target="_blank"
          >How To Make a Virtual "Frankenstein" Prototype Feat (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11299 mb-requirement-id-11301">
        (b) Create a model of the invention using clay, cardboard, or any other
        readily available material. List the materials necessary to build a
        working prototype of the invention. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/k_9Q-KDSb9o" target="_blank"
          >How To Make a Cardboard Prototype (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11299 mb-requirement-id-11302">
        (c) Share the idea and the model with your counselor and potential users
        of your invention. Record their feedback in your notebook.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11308">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Build a working prototype of the item you invented for requirement 6. Test
      and evaluate the invention. Among the aspects to consider in your
      evaluation are cost, usefulness, marketability, appearance, and function.
      Describe how your original vision and expectations for your invention are
      similar or dissimilar to the prototype you built. Have your counselor
      evaluate and critique your prototype.<br /><br /><b>Note: </b>Before you
      begin building the prototype, you must have your counselor's approval,
      based on the design and building plans you have already shared. <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/k_9Q-KDSb9o" target="_blank"
        >How To Build Prototypes! (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11303">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11303 mb-requirement-id-11304">
        (a) Participate with a club or team (robotics team, science club, or
        engineering club) that builds a useful item. Share your experience with
        your counselor. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Jd29kzjclV0" target="_blank"
          >About FIRST Robotics Competition (2021) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Mi6E37oU8yc" target="_blank"
          >About VEX Robotics (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11303 mb-requirement-id-11305">
        (b) Visit a museum or exhibit dedicated to an inventor or invention, and
        create a presentation of your visit to share with a group such as your
        troop or patrol. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://museumsdatabase.com/" target="_blank"
          >National Museum's Database (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.invent.org/museum/exhibits" target="_blank"
          >National Inventors Hall of Fame (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://invention.si.edu/" target="_blank"
          >Smithsonian's Lemelson Center (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.uspto.gov/about-us/uspto-locations/alexandria-va/national-inventors-hall-fame-and-museum"
          target="_blank"
          >National Inventors Hall of Fame and Museum (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11309">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor the diverse skills, education, training, and
      experience it takes to be an inventor. Discuss how you can prepare
      yourself to be creative and inventive to solve problems at home, in
      school, and in your community. Discuss three career fields that might
      utilize the skills of an inventor. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/WErRJ581SIQ" target="_blank"
        >Meaningful Soft Skills for Inventors (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/3sUHYD728s0" target="_blank"
        >What Does It Take To Be an Inventor? (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.zippia.com/inventor-jobs/best-companies-for-inventors/"
        target="_blank"
        >10 Best Companies for Inventors (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/ZKuNaN3Dqis" target="_blank"
        >Work of an Examinor (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Jm2rB29enN4" target="_blank"
        >Why a Career in Science Is for Me (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
